Author: Lennynpj <lenny93190@icloud.com>
Date:   Sun Apr 26 08:36:28 2026 +0200

    Dev D: API live fetch+analyze on cache miss GPS coords

    When POST /api/design receives {lat, lng} that don't match any pre-baked
    house within 50m, the API now spawns the bake pipeline live:
      1. pnpm bake:fetch with LIVE_HOUSE_ID/LAT/LNG env vars → downloads
         Google 3D Tiles for the ad-hoc address (~30-60s)
      2. pnpm bake:analyze:multi <liveId> → runs 22 variants + selection
         (~2-4min)
      3. Reads the generated analysis.json and returns standard response

    Generated houseId is stable: live-{lat6}-{lng6}, so subsequent requests
    for the same coords hit the cache instantly.

    Files:
    - src/app/api/design/route.ts: spawn child processes, route timeout 600s
    - src/scripts/fetch-3d-tiles.ts: accept LIVE_* env vars (alongside HOUSES list)
    - src/scripts/analyze-roof.ts: accept live-* IDs without HOUSES validation
    - public/baked/bench-berlin1-analysis.json: re-baked with new top-level
      fields from previous commit (no algo change)

    Knobs:
    - DISABLE_LIVE_FETCH=1 → reverts to 404 on cache miss (CI / read-only mode)
    - Live fetch consumes Google 3D Tiles quota (~\$0.005 per address)

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

